children.subject:
Hi Chris,

The maximum amount of students the labs can hold is 490. There are currently 483 students in 16A and 13 others who took the 16A pilot and still need 16B. This comes to 496. We have created 496 CECs so all of you can enroll.

Not all students who took 16A will need 16B e.g. LSCS students who only need 16A to graduate. There will also be some students who elect to take 16B in the fall, not to mention the usual attrition in the first few weeks of the semester that brings enrollment down. The odds are definitely in your favor to use Phase II.

That being said, it is always best practice to monitor the enrollment. If you have other classes you would rather Phase I, go ahead and then watch what happens with 16B. If you find that the enrollment is increasing and you would feel better using Phase I toward 16B since it's a required course, you can always change during Open Hours.
Is it possible to sign up during adjustment period and still get in?
If you have a CEC, yes. Having a CEC is the only way to enroll into 16B this spring.

Is there any case where it is required to phase 1, or can you guarantee we'll get in with phase 2? I'm asking because I would need it to graduate at the end of next semester so it's very important I get in.

Thanks!

If you are currently in 16A, they will be given out by the GSIs. If you took the 16A pilot, I will email the CEC to you.

This will be done in the next couple days.

Thanks for your patience!
How will we be receiving the class entry codes? Thanks!

history.content:
All students currently in 16A and those who took the 16A pilot and have not yet taken 16B will receive a Class Entry Code for 16B. Students without a CEC will not be able to enroll. If a CEC is given to a student who has not taken 16A, they will be dropped from 16B.
Since a CEC is required to enroll into 16B, you may use Phase II to enroll and use Phase I units for other classes.
We hope this answers questions and alleviates stress!
history.subject: 16B Enrollment Enrollment Procedure, Spring '16
